Terraform itself default region set cheyyadu.
Adi AWS CLI / environment nundi teesukuntundi.

Enduku region automatic ga vachindi?

Mee system lo already idi undi:

AWS_DEFAULT_REGION or

AWS_REGION or

AWS CLI config (~/.aws/config)

Example:

aws configure


Ippudu set chesina region ni Terraform silent ga use chesthundi.

Terraform region priority (actual flow):

1️⃣ provider "aws" { region = "..." }
2️⃣ Env vars → AWS_REGION / AWS_DEFAULT_REGION
3️⃣ AWS CLI config
4️⃣ ❌ Em lekapothe → error

Proof check cheyyali ante:
aws configure list





Without documentation:

User ki teliyadu:

Ee module em chesthundi

Which variables mandatory

Optional values enti

Wrong value isthe em avtundi

With documentation:

Clear ga telusthundi:

Inputs (variables)

Outputs

Example usage

Constraints (like your instance_type validation)

Real example (nee case):

Nuvvu module create chesav:

variable "instance_type" {
  validation {
    condition = contains(["t3.micro","t3.small","t3.medium"], var.instance_type)
  }
}


User ki documentation lo teliyali:

Allowed values: t3.micro, t3.small, t3.medium

Other values isthe → error vastundi

Industry reason:

Same module ni 100 mandi use chestharu

Andariki code open chesi chudadam possible kaadu

Documentation = contract between module author & user
